[1] Georgia (Tbilisi)
Date: Thu 9 May 2013
Source: NewsGeorgia [in Russian. trans.Mod.NP, edited]
http://newsgeorgia.ru/society/20130507/215675071.html


Number of persons infected with measles in Georgia exceeded 2600
---------------------------------------------------------
The number of people infected with measles in Georgia reached 2668 people, 835 of whom were hospitalized due to complications, according to the National Center for Disease Control and Public Health of Georgia. Georgia has recorded a significant increase in measles virus infections. An 11-month-old child and a 19-year-old male died on 7 May 2013 as [a result] of measles virus infection. Because of the threat of the epidemic, in early April [2013], the country began a free vaccination campaign against measles for people who have not been vaccinated earlier, as well as those in contact with patients. According to the center, in Georgia measles infected mainly persons from 20 to 29 years (950 cases). Measles has infected 565 people over 30 years of age, 302 teenagers aged 15 to 19 years, 176 teenagers between the ages of 10-14 years, 169 children between the ages of 5 and 9 years old and 323 children of 4 years of age and below. Also of measles was diagnosed in 183 children under one year of age.

Measles is an acute infectious viral disease that is characterized by high temperatures (up to 40.5 degrees C), inflammation of the mucous membranes of the mouth and upper respiratory tract, conjunctivitis and characteristic maculopapular skin rash, general intoxication. Measles is spread by airborne droplets, the virus is released into the environment in large quantities from a sick person with mucus during coughing, sneezing, etc.

