[2] Georgia (Tbilisi)
Date: Tue 7 May 2013
Source: Novostimira.com [In Russian, trans. Mod.NP, edited]
http://novostimira.com/novosti_mira_55324.html


In Georgia now 3150 cases of measles
--------------------------------
Today, the National Center for Disease Control and Public Health of Georgia reported that in the last 14 days more than a thousand cases of measles had been recorded. To date, the number of cases has exceeded 3150 people, 985 of whom were hospitalized. Most cases were recorded in the Georgian capital Tbilisi, where the number of cases is now 205. In addition, cases of measles virus infection were recorded in 48 cities and regions of the country. All of these data are provided by the Georgian medical authorities. Measles affects people of all ages, from children to the elderly. More than a thousand cases were people from 20 to 29 years old. Already there have been 2 deaths, an 11-month-old girl and a 19-year-old male. Currently the Center cannot predict precisely when the epidemic will subside.

